#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SWIR.rst:4
#: b660e6e4be9c4f12a920c0024a65f90c
msgid ""
"The SWIR Model [1]_ extends the classic SIR framework by introducing a "
"**Weakened (W)** state between Susceptible (S) and Infected (I). Infection "
"spreads only through links between neighboring nodes in a graph "
":math:`G=(V,E)`. Each node is in one of four states: :math:`S` "
"(susceptible), :math:`W` (weakened), :math:`I` (infected), or :math:`R` "
"(recovered). At a high level, a susceptible node can either be weakened or "
"directly infected by its infected neighbors; weakened nodes can subsequently"
" become infected; infected nodes recover and become immune (R). The model is"
" parameterized by three per-contact rates: :math:`\\kappa` (direct "
"infection), :math:`\\mu` (weakening), and :math:`\\nu` (weak-to-infected)."
msgstr ""
"SWIR模型[1] 扩展经典的SIR框架,在可感知(S)和受感染(I)之间引入**微弱(W)**状态. "
"感染只通过相邻节点之间的联系在图:`G=(V,E)'中传播。 每个节点在四个状态中之一: "
"发音:`S'(疑似),发音:`W'(微弱),发音:`I'(感染),或发音:`R'(恢复). "
"在高水平上,易感节点可以被其感染的邻居削弱或直接感染;弱节点随后会感染;感染的节点恢复并免疫(R). "
"该模型以3个每接触率参数::math:`\\kappa'(直接感染),math:`\\mu'(微弱),math:`\\nu'(微弱感染)."

